  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign spanning 128 Latin-hypercube sample points was conducted to characterise parametric sensitivity across impeller tip clearance, volute geometry, and inlet flow angle; results are summarised in the validation report VR-CPB-2026-01 and inform the factor rationales below.",
