    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are within the scope of acceptable non-assessment at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. Validation results demonstrate RH predictions within ±15% of experimental data across all five operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion at worst-case conditions. The UQ campaign (summarised in VR-CPB-2026-01) confirmed that critical geometric parameters are adequately bounded by manufacturing inspection data. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for this Class II CPB device.",
